# rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (8, 5)
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score

wcss = []

for i in range(2, 10):
    
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i, random_state=84, n_init='auto')
    kmeans.fit(country_scaled)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
    cluster_labels = kmeans.labels_

    pca = PCA(n_components=2)
    principal_components = pca.fit_transform(country_scaled)
    pca_df = pd.DataFrame(data=principal_components, columns=['PC1', 'PC2'])
    pca_df['cluster'] = cluster_labels

    unique_labels = np.unique(cluster_labels)

    plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))
    for label in unique_labels:
        #plt.scatter(country_scaled[cluster_labels = label, 0], country_scaled[cluster_labels == label, 1], label = f'Cluster {label}')
        subset = pca_df[pca_df['cluster'] == label]
        plt.scatter(subset['PC1'], subset['PC2'], label=f'Cluster {label}')

    plt.scatter(kmeans.cluster_centers_[:,0], kmeans.cluster_centers_[:,1], marker='h', s=200, color='black', label='Centroids')
    plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')
    plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')
    plt.title('Principal Component Analysis of Data with Cluster Labels')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(pca_df, cluster_labels)
    print(f'Silhouette Score: {silhouette_avg}')
